#: {{uxi|fr|Je le défends '''autant que''' je puis.|t=I defend it '''as much as''' I can.}}
#* {{quote-journal|fr|url=https://www.cairn.info/revue-relations-internationales-2011-1-page-53.htm|title=L'Asie central vue de Chine|trans-title=Central Asia viewed from China|year=2011|journal=Relations internationales|volume=145|pages=53—70|text=les pays d'Asie centrale ne s'investissent pas '''autant que''' la Chine dans l'Organisation de coopération de Shanghai.|t=The countries of Central Asia are not '''as''' invested '''as much as''' China [is] in the Shanghai Cooperation Organization.|author=Jean-Pierre Cabestan}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|year=1857|author=Phillippe Athanase Cucheval-Clarigny|title=Histoire de la presse en Angleterre et aux États-Unis|page=472|passage=Réunies en volumes, ces lettres ont été goûtées en Angleterre presque '''autant qu'''{{'}}aux États-Unis, et ont eu plusieurs éditions.|t=Collected into volumes, these letters have been appreciated in England '''as much as''' in the United States, and have had several editions.}}
# [[as well as]]
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Nicolas Boileau|title=Le Lutrin|volume=IV|year=1683|text=Pour moi, je lis la Bible '''autant que''' l'Alcoran.|t=As for me, I read the Bible '''as well as''' the Quran.}}
# [[just as well]], [[might as well]]/[[may as well]]
#: {{uxi|fr|Je n'ai rien à vous dire, alors autant que vous gardiez le silence.|t=I have nothing to say to you, so you '''might as well''' keep silent.}}

====Usage notes====
The verb that follows '''autant que''' may be in the subjunctive form.

